{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Generate Tests from Codebase",
  "description": "Scans the app's source code (Compose, SwiftUI, XML layouts), identifies screens, interactive elements, and user flows, then generates reusable YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder with cross-platform support.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Scan the mobile app source code in this workspace. Find all UI source files — look for: Kotlin Compose (*.kt with @Composable), SwiftUI (*.swift with View protocol/body), XML layouts (res/layout/*.xml), UIKit storyboards/xibs. STEP 1 — SCAN & UNDERSTAND: Identify all screens, activities, fragments, navigation flows, interactive elements, API calls, authentication logic, and data models. Understand the full app architecture before generating anything. STEP 2 — AUTO-GENERATE prompt/*.md: Based on what you found in the codebase, create the prompt/ folder and generate these context files: a) prompt/flow-order.md — ordered list of user flows based on navigation graph and dependencies (e.g., login must come before home screen tests). b) prompt/credentials.md — identify what credentials/test data are needed based on auth logic found in code. If code uses email+password login, define test credentials. If code has guest mode, note that. c) prompt/workarounds.md — note any known automation challenges found in code (e.g., custom views that may not be accessible, WebViews, animations that need waits). d) prompt/app-context.md — brief summary of what the app does, key features, package name, main entry points. e) prompt/testability.md — list ALL identified flows categorized as: TESTABLE (can be fully automated: UI interactions, navigation, form validation, state checks) vs NOT TESTABLE (cannot be automated: requires OTP/email verification not accessible via API, requires payment with real money, requires physical hardware like camera/biometrics, requires server-side state that can't be set from client). For each non-testable flow, explain WHY and what would be needed to make it testable. STEP 3 — READ prompt/*.md back and use as context for generation. STEP 4 — GENERATE TEST SCRIPTS: For each screen found: 1) Identify all interactive elements with accessibility labels. 2) Identify user flows and state changes. 3) Determine platform (Kotlin/XML → android; Swift → ios). 4) Generate test scripts with QUALITY OVER QUANTITY mindset. PRIORITIZE: critical user flows, error states users actually encounter, state transitions that could break. AVOID: redundant tests, trivial tests, tests that overlap significantly. Each test must be UNIQUE and test something MEANINGFULLY DIFFERENT. Aim for 2-3 high-value test cases per feature. Each must have detailed steps and SPECIFIC expected results. 5) Save YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder following the schema in the generate-from-codebase steering file. Order by flow (from prompt/flow-order.md). 6) Generate e2e-tests/coverage.yaml listing all elements and coverage. 7) Read e2e-tests/version.yaml — if exists, increment version by 1; if not, set to 1. Save updated version.yaml. Output a summary of: screens found, elements identified, prompt files generated, test scripts generated."
  }
}